         </item-info>
         <ce:floats>
            <ce:figure id="f0005">
               <ce:label>Fig. 1</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0005">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0005" view="all">Study Site.</ce:simple-para>
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0010" view="all">
                     <ce:cross-ref id="cf0005" refid="f0005">Fig. 1</ce:cross-ref>: Areas of restoration, identified by treatment type, within the Cosumnes River Preserve where C values were determined. Plots where biomass was measured in 2020–21, including the 48 plots repeated from 2012–13, are identified with a green ‘tree’ triangle icon while plots with only litter and soil are identified with a yellow circle ‘soil core’ icon. All biomass plots shown here also included litter and soil measurements. Plots that were only measured in 2012–13 are not included here, but can be found in <ce:bold>Appendix A</ce:bold>. The CRP boundaries are identified with a dark green outline.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0005">Fig. 1</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0005" locator="gr1" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="pii:S0048969724039767/gr1" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="f0010">
               <ce:label>Fig. 2</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0010">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0015" view="all">Plot biomass compared to plot BA in 2012 (a) and 2020 (b).</ce:simple-para>
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0020" view="all">
                     <ce:cross-ref id="cf0010" refid="f0010">Fig. 2</ce:cross-ref>: Plot biomass (Mg ha<ce:sup loc="post">-1</ce:sup>) X BA (m<ce:sup loc="post">2</ce:sup> ha<ce:sup loc="post">−1</ce:sup>) in 2012 (a) and 2020 (b) with the outlier included to provide context. Scales between the 2012 and 2020 are uniform, as are the color indicators for treatment across both plots. The log-log transform is provided in the inset for both 2012 and 2020.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0010">Fig. 2</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0010" locator="gr2" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="pii:S0048969724039767/gr2" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="f0015">
               <ce:label>Fig. 3</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0015">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0025" view="all">Litter &amp; Soil Collection.</ce:simple-para>
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0030" view="all">
                     <ce:cross-ref id="cf0015" refid="f0015">Fig. 3</ce:cross-ref>: (a) Litter sample boundary deliniated from surrounding litter, (b) litter sample collected to soil surface, and (c) center-point of litter collection identified for soil sample collection.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0015">Fig. 3</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0015" locator="gr3" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="pii:S0048969724039767/gr3" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="f0020">
               <ce:label>Fig. 4</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0020">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0035" view="all">Total C.</ce:simple-para>
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0040" view="all">
                     <ce:cross-ref id="cf0020" refid="f0020">Fig. 4</ce:cross-ref>: Total C for each plot, grouped by treatment type, with stocks distinguished by color. Biomass C is olive, Litter C is magenta, and Soil C is in limoncello.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0020">Fig. 4</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0020" locator="gr4" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="pii:S0048969724039767/gr4" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="f0025">
               <ce:label>Fig. 5</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0025">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0045" view="all">Soil C X C:N by Grain Size.</ce:simple-para>
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0050" view="all">
                     <ce:cross-ref id="cf0025" refid="f0025">Fig. 5</ce:cross-ref>: (a.) The C value within each grain size is compared to the C:N ratio of the given soil grain fraction. (b.) Because the C:N ratio facilitates mineralization and C sequestration, the non-linear relationship, especially within the &lt;2 mm soil fraction, is indicative of the potential for microbial digestion to occur within a given soil fraction.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0025">Fig. 5</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0025" locator="gr5" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="pii:S0048969724039767/gr5" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="f0030">
               <ce:label>Fig. 6</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0030">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0055" view="all">Carbon by Pool.</ce:simple-para>
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0060" view="all">
                     <ce:cross-ref id="cf0030" refid="f0030">Fig. 6</ce:cross-ref>: Each C stock grouped by treatment type: AG = Agriculture, AST = Assisted, HYD = Hybrid, PRO = Process, RMT = Remnant. All measurements are in Mg ha<ce:sup loc="post">−1</ce:sup>. Outliers mentioned directly are denoted by a *.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0030">Fig. 6</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0030" locator="gr6" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="pii:S0048969724039767/gr6" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="f0035">
               <ce:label>Fig. 7</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0035">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0065" view="all">Carbon through Time.</ce:simple-para>
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0070" view="all">
                     <ce:cross-ref id="cf0035" refid="f0035">Fig. 7</ce:cross-ref>: Carbon stocks by treatment and time since year zero. The y-axis is log scaled and all measurements are in Mg ha<ce:sup loc="post">−1</ce:sup>. Though there is a general trend evident in the median lines within the boxplots, the overall lower positions of the Assisted compared to the Process type stocks in the &lt;40 year plots is of special note. This plot is further broken down into treatment type within each decade group in <ce:bold>Appendix D</ce:bold>.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0035">Fig. 7</ce:alt-text>
               <ce:link id="lk0035" locator="gr7" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="pii:S0048969724039767/gr7" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:table xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/cals/dtd" id="t0005" frame="topbot" rowsep="0" colsep="0">
               <ce:label>Table 1</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="ca0040">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0075" view="all">Literature on Carbon in Mediterranean Riparian Forests.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text role="short" id="al0040">Table 1</ce:alt-text>
               <tgroup cols="4">
                  <colspec colname="col1"/>
